No part of this manual may be reproduced or transmitted in any form or by any means, electronic or
mechanical, including photocopying and recording, for any purpose without the express written
permission of Lund University School of Aviation.
A special thank you to our author and coder, Oskar Ardryd & Joakim Kjellander from TFHS20. The
purpose of this CTM is to make it easy and recognizable for the students to know how the exercises
in 51xx should be performed. We hope that this document will be passed down from the senior
classes to their junior classes in the future. It is of the highest priority that this document is not
published in any other forums than TFHS class specific groups and is not presented to junior class
until after 5101 is completed.
Exercise 5101-5109 may not be deleted but can be interpreted differently by the students to fit their
desire. It is accepted and appreciated if future students contribute and add new exercises.
The order of the exercises is not a requirement, but the order is recommended and is backed by
experience. The ATPL and beechparty order can be changed if there are non-completed tests or
exercises. Tmningen is another exercise that can be moved and arranged multiple times a year if
needed.

MPL Core 5101 Nollning
Objective
The Student shall with assistance of its class mates complete a series of tasks presented by the class
above.
The student must show certain skills needed as a pilot.
The student shall compete with each other to determine who is the best.
Weather
Hopefully good, but any weather is accepted.
Crosswind component suitable for training but not more than OM.
Scenario
Students are assigned into multiple groups, they shall NOT communicate with other groups and this
will be interpreted as cheating and will be punished. Students will be presented with instructions that
they will have to follow the coming hours.
Majority of tasks will be located outside, time will be limited for students to find and regroup on the
next location. They will be supplied with alcohol that has to be consumed from one station to another.
Norweigan christmas (see PSG) is the second activity and will be held after the first tasks are
completed. The teams compete with each other and the winner will compete with a team from the
senior class.
Dinner will be served and provided by the senior class. There will be sufficient time for showers and
making yourself look presentable for dinner.
Plankgng (See PSG) is the final exercise within the teams, where the 2 best teams compete in the
corridors of Ljunghusen.
Last exercise to be presented is the visual landing during the influence of alcohol. After a successful
landing is done by the student, he/she must consume a shot of alcohol. If completed to the set
standard, the student shall be rewarded with a pair of TFHS-klaffar.
The exercise will end with a night at ISOBAR where students will be interrogated by Kapten.

MPL Core 5102 ATPL fest
Objective
Senior class shall celebrate the completion of ATPL-theories.
Present the amount of time spent on AviationExam/Atplq.
Elimination of the EQCB used during ATPL.
Sacrifice one part of ATPL to the Theory Goods.
Weather
Hopefully good due to outside activities and BBQ(optional).
Scenario
Event will be booked after all students have completed ATPL-theory and are ready to say goodbye to
their question bank.
The event will start at a reasonable time, to maximize the amount of hours available for alcohol
consumption.
After sunset the sacrifice will commence and a bonfire will be created.
Evening will end in ISOBAR.
Preparation
1. Full completion of ATPL theory.
2. Prepare IPAD with question bank and retrieve your progress.
3. Prepare a symbolic object for sacrifice (eg, notes, jeppesen etc).

MPL Core 5103 or MPL Core 2121 Beechfest
Objective
The student shall tacka ja to the event
The student shall perform a correct serve from the serve line within half scale deflections and +-5ft in
zero wind conditions
The student shall explain the necessity of drinking while playing and the effects of dehydration without
assistance from the instructor
The student shall explain with reference to memory the minimum units required for a successful night
given by the OM
Weather
Hopefully good due to outside activities and BBQ(optional).
Scenario
To introduce the basics of beechvolleyboll
1. LOB at 1300z
2. T/O and SID to field
3. Play beechvolleyboll
4. Have fun
5. Go around, play more beechvolleyboll
6. Enjoy BBQ and pray for tomorrow
Preparation
Cold drinks and a happy mind

MPL Core 5104 Paddling
Objective
Take on the notorious Rnne in a kayak.
Take down your enemies.
Survie .
Weather
Preferably good weather. We can manage IMC/SVFR if no other option is available.
Scenario
The student shall team up with one or two classmates, disguised(see next point), and travel down the
notorious Rnne supplied with their own beverages
Its of the highest priority that we are NOT recognized as students due to our profession.
After Rnne has been defeated a gruesome ride back to Ljungbyhed is done on a Dressin.
Preparation
1. Acquire a disguise, extra points if a boat is has the same theme
2. Acquire the alcoholic beverage of your choice.
3. Bring a bag for trash disposal. We must not leave cans or other trash along our journey.
4. A hat is recommended if CAVOK.

MPL Core 5105 Tackfest
Objective
Act as a butler towards the senior class students.
Show appreciation towards senior class.
Arrangement of a successful dinner.
Have Fun.
Weather
Not applicable.
Scenario
Students shall show appreciation towards the senior class, as a thank you for exercise
5101-Nollning by all means.
A femkamp shall be arranged for senior class.
Students in junior class shall arrange a dinner and provide the senior class with beverages and be
available at all times.
The senior classs wish is the junior classs command.
Preparation
1. A theme for the exercise shall be decided by the junior class. The theme must be defined by a
letter and be presented to senior class well in advance of the exercise. Costumes must be
prepared for this exercise.
2. The Femkamps activities may be themed at students' own discretion. Activities shall be
equipped with alcoholic beverages for the attendees.
3. An aviation related sign MUST be acquired before exercise by the junior class. This act must
be recorded and displayed to the senior class, preferably during dinner. It is of highest priority
that the sign is handed over to senior class and that cover is not blown during operation. The
sign must not be in the local area of operation (outside of ESTL control zone).

MPL Core 5106a Tequila
Objective
Work hard at ppet hus at day, Play hard at night
Wear sombrero
Consume Mexican food and alcoholic beverages
Weather
Preferably good weather, any weather is acceptable
Scenario
Student shall attend the yearly ppet hus during the day, answering ridiculous questions (most
likely related to MPL) and in the meantime long towards the evening.
After completion of ppet hus, rush their way towards ljunghusen and change to a typical mexican
outfit.
Prepare and devour typical mexican food
Preparation
1. Student shall study applicable PSG and MMEL for this exercise.
2. Student must study different techniques for cooking tacos and folding a tortilla
Threat and Error Management and discussion points.
The following items must be prepared thoroughly before the long briefing. The outcome of the
discussion must be presented at the long briefing.
Excessive consumption of tequila
Incorrect technique used for folding a tortilla
Not understanding spanish

MPL Core 5106b Krftskivan
Objective
Attend a krftskiva that is arranged in ljunghusen
Wear a matching hat
Advised to eat crayfish
Get drunk
Weather
Not applicable, could be arranged both out and inside.
Scenario
An alternate exercise to 5106a, introduced during Covid-19 pandemic due to no ppet hus.
Student shall show skill in preparing, peeling and eating crayfish
Preparation
Acquire necessities for a krftskiva, either alone or in a team.
Prepare dining area with a lngbord and matching decoration
Threat and Error Management and discussion points.
The following items must be prepared thoroughly before the long briefing. The outcome of the
discussion must be presented at the long briefing.
Not using the right technique for peeling crayfish and poking your neighbors eye
Not throwing out the trash
Incorrect usage of SHOT-HATT

MPL Core 5107 Julbord
Objective
A gigantic Julbord shall be arranged by the Senior class the last weekend before Junior class have
their PEXO.
Christmas is celebrated, students must prepare the most crucial types of food, appetizers, mulled
wine and snacks to maximize the christmas spirit
Weather
Not applicable
Scenario
During the last weekend before the junior class has their school tests in PEXO block 2, the senior
class shall prepare a christmas feast for all to enjoy, accompanied by christmas decoration.
Everything from ribs, christmas ham, flying jacob, prinskorv, potatis and swedish meatballs. Mulled
wine is served by senior class and is accompanied by ginger bread, lussebullar and other classic
christmas sweets.
Its not a requirement, but isobar can be opened at your own discretion. Closing early is accepted due
to skolprov.
Preparation
Enough food for all attendants must be bought by a designated group from senior class
Food teams are set up at their own discretion by the senior students, and different areas of
responsibilities are distributed.
Threat and Error Management and discussion points.
The following items must be prepared thoroughly before the long briefing. The outcome of the
discussion must be presented at the long briefing.
Not driving below the speed limit when transporting the christmas ham
Not studying ATPL and failing pexo

MPL Core 5108 Hejd
Objective
One last party shall be arranged to thank the senior class for the past year and wish them
good luck in the future.
Isobar must be opened and everyone must attend and contribute to one last great party.
Weather
Party is scheduled after winter break, IFR is the most probable TAF decoder, but weather is
disregarded due to indoor activities
Scenario
Students in the junior class shall arrange one last party with the senior class, before the senior class
leave ljunghusen for FFS. One last dinner should be arranged to make the most out of the last night,
this should be accompanied with songs, spex, pictures and or memories from the past year. The
students' imagination can only set the limit.
The evening will end in ISOBAR as SOP states and shall be closed(according to SOP) LATE. During
the ISOBAR-stage, the senior class should sign the walls of ISOBAR with a quote of their choice and
accompanied with their nametag/callsign.
Preparation
Food must be ordered, bought or prepared. Catering is recommended.
Alcohol is not a must, but greatly appreciated.
A good seating config is advantageous, preferably : SENIOR JUNIOR SENIOR JUNIOR

MPL Core 5109 Tmningen
Objective
Students shall work as a group to empty ISOBAR with any means necessary before the refill
operation is commenced.
Weather
Not applicable
Scenario
A tmning shall be prepared when the stockpiles of the mighty isobar reach the critical point.
ISOBAR has reduced or eliminated the prices to make room for new alcohol.
Preparation
ISOBAR-kungen must do a check of the stockpile for planning purposes and determine how much he
can reduce the prices at the bar
No other preparations are needed
Threat and Error Management and discussion points.
The following items must be prepared thoroughly before the long briefing. The outcome of the
discussion must be presented at the long briefing.
ISOBAR not having enough alcohol
Not contributing to the event resulting in a overloaded ISOBAR
